h3. Summary

When creating issue link to a issue from another JIRA instance (connected through an application link), the issue will not be displayed on the *Links* column in the issue navigator.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create an application link between two JIRA instances;
# Create a issue on each instance;
# Create an issue link between these two issues (one on each server);

h3. Expected Results

The issue link is displayed on the *Links* column.

h3. Actual Results

Only issue links from within that JIRA instance will be displayed.

Similar to https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-71153 but this API is for creating and updating issues.

The Jira REST API for creating and updating issues should allow you to assign an issue to the default assignee by specifying "-1", according to the documentation. 

e.g. 

HTTP POST to /rest/api/2/issue

This works when specifying the assignee by name:

{code:java}
{
	"fields": {
		"assignee": {
			"name": "-1"
		},
		"project": {
			"key": "TES"
		},
		"issuetype": {
			"id": "10004"
		},
		"summary": "hello"
	}

}
{code}

but not when specifying the assignee by account ID.

{code:java}
{
	"fields": {
		"assignee": {
			"id": "-1"
		},
		"project": {
			"key": "TES"
		},
		"issuetype": {
			"id": "10004"
		},
		"summary": "hello"
	}

}
{code}

If you send the personal data JQL migration endpoint a query like "assignee = brooke" it returns the account ID in parentheses, like "assignee = (abcde-12345)". This is effectively changing a single term into a list, which causes an error when Jira tries to parse the new JQL.

{quote}
Operator '=' does not support the list value '("abcde-12345")' for field 'assignee'.
{quote}

It should be possible to send ad-hoc notifications using the /rest/api/2/issue/<id>/notify REST API, specifying users by account ID, but this fails with an internal server error.
{code:java}
"to": {
    "reporter": false,
    "assignee": false,
    "watchers": true,
    "voters": true,
    "users": [
      {
        "accountId": "abcde-12345",
        "active": false
      }
    ]
{code}

h3. Summary
In the new issue editor of Jira Cloud, entering strings that contain '...\!....' end up escaping the \ character when this is not always the intention of the end user.  



h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Enter a string into a comment or description of a Jira issue such as {code:borderStyle=solid}
c:\!test\world 
{code}
# Save the change


h3. Expected Results
In the previous editor, it would display correctly as intended 
{code:borderStyle=solid}
c:\!test\world 
{code}


h3. Actual Results
The editor is escaping the \ which makes the path invalid and inaccurate
c:!test\world


h3. Notes


h3.Workaround
Using a Code block will show the string correctly {noformat} {code}
c:\!test\world 
{code}
{noformat}

OR

Using the other slash such as '/' instead can still allow the text to display correctly, and in the case of filepaths, still be used in Windows environments. {code}
c:/!test/world 
{code}

h3. Problem Definition

/rest/api/3/search does not return comment.body and worklog.body fields rendered in HTML even if we pass parameter expand=renderedFields.. This works well in Rest API v2
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Call the search endpoint version 2 in order to return some issues with comments and worklog like, e.g.: [https://INSTANCE-URL/rest/api/2/search?jql=project%20%3D%20TRP%20ORDER%20BY%20key%20ASC&fields=comment,description,summary,worklog&expand=renderedFields|https://instance-url/rest/api/2/search?jql=project%20%3D%20TRP%20ORDER%20BY%20key%20ASC&fields=comment,description,summary,worklog&expand=renderedFields]
 # See that the above endpoint returns the worklogs and comment details in HTML:
{noformat}
[...]
      "key": "TRP-1",
      "renderedFields": {
        "summary": null,
        "description": "<p>DESCRIPTION</p>\n\n",
        "comment": {
          "comments": [
            {
              "self": "https://xxxxx.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/10504/comment/10218",
              "id": "10218",
              "author": {
                "self": [...]
                },
                "displayName": "[...]
                [...]
              },
              "body": "<p>comment</p>",
[...]
        "worklog": {
          "startAt":[...]
           [...]
          "worklogs": [
            {
              "self": [...]
              },
              "updateAuthor": {
                "name": "ID10850",
                "active": false
              },
              "comment": "<p>Logged one day of work…</p>\n\n<p>Still 2 days to go&#33;</p>",
[...]
{noformat}

 # Run the same search query using the V3 endpoint: [https://INSTANCE-URL/rest/api/3/search?jql=project%20%3D%20TRP%20ORDER%20BY%20key%20ASC&fields=comment,description,summary,worklog&expand=renderedFields|https://instance-url/rest/api/3/search?jql=project%20%3D%20TRP%20ORDER%20BY%20key%20ASC&fields=comment,description,summary,worklog&expand=renderedFields]

h3. Expected results

The same body as v2 is returned
h3. Actual result

The worklog comments body is missing and the issue comments body is not rendered:
{noformat}
[...]
      "key": "TRP-1",
      "renderedFields": {
        "summary": null,
        "description": "<p>DESCRIPTION</p>\n\n",
        "comment": {
          "comments": [
            {
              "self": "https://xxxxxxx.atlassian.net/rest/api/3/issue/10504/comment/10218",
              "id": "10218",
              "author": {
               [...]
                },
                "displayName": "[...]
                [...]
              },
              "body": {
                "version": 1,
                "type": "doc",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "comment"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
[...]
        "worklog": {
         "startAt":[...]
           [...]
          "worklogs": [
            {
              "self": [...]
              },
              "updateAuthor": {
                "name": "ID10850",
                "active": false
              },
              "created": "Today 12:56 PM",
              "updated": "Today 12:56 PM",
              "started": "Today 4:56 AM",
              "timeSpent": "1 day",
              "id": "10003",
              "issueId": "10504"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
{noformat}
h3.  
h3. Workaround

Two possible workarounds:
 # Use the v2 endpoint. 
 # Another way to get the comment body returned as HTML is to call [the GET /rest/api/3/[ISSUE KEY or ID]/comments|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/#api-rest-api-3-issue-issueIdOrKey-comment-get] endpoint and append *?**expand=renderedBody* to it. This way you get something like:
 {noformat}
"renderedBody": "<p>SOME COMMENT<br/>\nTEST BODY<br/>\nsadff<br/>\ndffffffffffffff</p>\n\n<p>istamana</p>\n\n<p>I write a comment</p>",
{noformat}

Unluckily this does not work for worklogs comments.

